Definition: an offering of common stock to existing shareholders who hold subscription rights or pre-emptive rights that entitle them to buy newly issued shares at a discount from the price at which they will be offered to the public later
Example: the investment banker who handles a rights offering usually agrees to buy any shares not bought by shareholders
Synonyms: rights_issue, offer, an, offering, of, common, stock, to, existing, shareholders, who, hold, subscription, rights, or, pre-emptive, that, entitle, them, buy, newly, issued, shares, at, a, discount, from, the, price, which, they, will, be, offered, public, later, investment, banker, handles, usually, agrees, any, not, bought, by
Category: noun.communication
